### Login with an unregistered or wrong-password user (regression guard).
### Validates the Error.AuthenticationRequired(ReasonCode) adoption from commit f808d1e
### (reg-001 shipped in Trellis 3.0.0-alpha.342).
### The "code" field in the problem-details body MUST be "Authentication.InvalidCredentials"
### — pre-alpha.342 it was just "unauthorized" because the closed Error union had no slot
### for a per-instance machine code on AuthenticationRequired.

POST {{host}}/authentication/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "userId": "xavierjohn2023",
    "password": "WrongPassword!"
}

### Expected response shape:
### HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized
### Content-Type: application/problem+json
### WWW-Authenticate: Bearer
### {
###   "type":"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc9110#section-15.5.2",
###   "title":"Unauthorized",
###   "status":401,
###   "detail":"Invalid credentials.",
###   "instance":"/authentication/login",
###   "code":"Authentication.InvalidCredentials",
###   "kind":"unauthorized"
### }
